Key

  • ends : The pale ends of the segments represent the trimmed regions that cath-resolve-hits may let overlap. Segments shorter than the min-seg-length are shown all pale.
  • colours : The hits' colours represent their calculation score: red is 0; green is the best score in the input hits (which may nevertheless be a "bad" hit).
  • grey : Grey hits represent hits with scores that have not met the --worst-permissible-[...] filters.
